article.headline: Sacramento St. 72, Idaho St. 69
article.story: SACRAMENTO, Calif. -- Junior Justin Eller's 12 points and 12 rebounds helped Sacramento State end a 14-game losing streak with a 72-69 win over Idaho State on Saturday night. Senior Loren Leath led the Hornets with 22 points and Randy Adams added 15 for the Sacramento State Hornets (2-19, 1-7 Big Sky), who gave first-year coach Brian Katz his first conference victory. Amorrow Morgan had 19 points and Donnie Carson scored 14 points for the Idaho State Bengals (7-14, 4-3 Big Sky), who ended a three-game winning streak. Junior Jonathan Malloy hit a 3-pointer with 1.6 seconds left in the first half to give the Hornets a 42-27 lead. The game was tied 13-13 at the 12:09 mark before the Hornets ended the first half, outscoring the Bengals 29-14. The Hornets built an 18-point lead early in the second half, but the Bengals fought back, cutting the margin to 68-65 on a basket by Carson with 22 seconds to play. Two free throws each by Leath and Antonio Flaggs with 30 seconds left in the game sealed the win for the Hornets.
